<section class="calm">				
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-offset-2 col-lg-8">
			<h2 class="section-heading">Champions for Change</h2>
			<div class="panel panel-default"><div class="panel-body">
			<p class="lead">The Change Champion Scholarship Programme is Coder Factory’s solution to every company’s diversity problem.</p> 
			<p>Recent reports show that the percentage of women in programming and software engineering roles is as low as 13%. There are so many great reasons why the world needs more women in technical roles. Here are just six of them:</p>
			<div class="highlight">
				<h3>Why we need more women in tech.</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>We need more people in tech, period.</li>
					<li>There will be less sexual harassment and discomfort when there are more women around.</li>
					<li>There will be less discrimination if it's not considered unusual for women to pursue tech careers.</li>
					<li>More women in tech now will encourage more girls to pursue their own interest in tech (and will therefore enable greater equality).</li>
					<li>A current lack of innovation in industries because there are fewer women in tech.</li>
					<li>Women think, act, and approach problems differently.</li>
				</ol>
				<small>Source: <a href="https://www.quora.com/Why-do-we-need-more-women-in-technology/answer/Gayle-Laakmann-McDowell?srid=dmne&share=1" target="_blank">Gayle McDowell</a> (Quora)</small>
			</div>
			</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="">				
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-offset-2 col-lg-8">
			<h2 class="section-heading dark">WHY?</h2>
